paragraphs.english:
It turns out that Lin Daiyu, despite her severe illness, was still somewhat aware. At the beginning, when Shiji and Xueyan were talking, she had also heard half of it but didn't respond due to a lack of energy. After hearing Shiji and Xueyan, she realized that the matter mentioned earlier was just a discussion and had not been decided. Additionally, since Shiji said it was what the Second Lady said, and the Old Lady's intention was to have her sister marry Baoyu and live in the garden, who else could it be? Therefore, upon thinking about it, her illness improved, and her mind became clearer, so she drank two mouthfuls of water and then wanted to ask Shiji. Just as the Old Lady, Madam Wang, Liwan, and the Second Lady heard Zhumu's words and came to see her, the doubts in her heart were already resolved, so she did not look like someone who wanted to commit suicide. Although she was weak and lacked energy, she still managed to answer a few questions. Fengzhoushi called over Zhumu and asked, "Why would you be like this? What happened? You are frightening people." Zhumu said, "Actually, I only went to tell you when I saw her not well. Later, when I saw she had improved a lot, I felt strange." The Old Lady laughed and said, "Don't blame her. She knows nothing, just that she dares to speak when she sees something wrong, which is her clear-headedness. It's good for a child not to be lazy with their mouth or feet." After talking for a while, when the Old Lady and others felt that there was nothing wrong, they left. As it was:

Due to the root of the illness, it was indeed for the sake of kinship;

And for that kinship matter, it was instead like saying someone had died.
